oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Carroll County Courthouse
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the second Carroll County Courthouse. The building later burned in 1931. A mule-drawn wagon is parked outside the fence. Note the hanging street light to the left of the courthouse.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Courthouses; Mules; Carts & wagons
